

# Aurora Recon Framework
Automated reconnaissance framework for penetration testing and CTF environments.
Designed to structure initial enumeration into a repeatable, fast and modular workflow.
> Authorized use only.
---
## Overview
Aurora automates the early-stage reconnaissance phase:
- Network discovery (Nmap)
- Service classification
- Context-based enumeration modules
- Structured output for analysis and reporting
Each scan generates a self-contained workspace with raw outputs and a consolidated report.
---
## Usage
```bash
python3 aurora.py -t <IP> [options]

⸻

Options

Target

-t / --target     Target IP or hostname

Scan modes

--fast            Top 100 ports scan
--full            Full port range scan (1–65535)

Workflow control

--quick           Run Nmap only (skip post-enumeration modules)
--silent          Suppress console output (scripting mode)

Environment presets

--htb             Hack The Box mode:
                  - optimized wordlists (SecLists)
                  - reduced timeout

Notes / Loot

--notes "text"    Add manual notes to report
                  (repeatable flag)

Output

-o / --output     Output directory

⸻

Output Structure

Each execution creates an isolated workspace:

aurora_<target>_<timestamp>/
├── nmap.txt
├── http_<port>.txt
├── smb.txt
├── ssh_<port>.txt
└── report.json

⸻

Report Structure

The final report aggregates scan results and manual input:

{
  "tool": "Aurora v4.3",
  "target": "10.10.10.10",
  "mode": "fast",
  "summary": {
    "ports": 3,
    "modules": 2
  },
  "loot": {
    "notes": [
      "admin panel found at /admin",
      "anonymous FTP enabled"
    ],
    "credentials": [],
    "interesting": []
  }
}

⸻

Design Principles

* Modular service-based enumeration
* No external dependencies (system tools only)
* Reproducible output per target
* Separation between raw data and structured findings
* Manual analyst input supported via loot system

⸻

Intended Use

* Hack The Box / TryHackMe environments
* OSCP-style labs
* Internal lab environments
* Initial enumeration phase automation

